The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Saturday, August 14, 2004 				 SC prods panel for police probe
 OUR BUREAU																								New Delhi, Aug. 13: The Supreme Court today directed the state human rights commission to file an affidavit detailing its inquiry into alleged Calcutta police excesses on three freedom fighters.																								The commission had given a clean chit to the force, which had in January 2002 lathi-charged a procession against the polices rights violations led by social activists, including Sunil Pal, Ashalata Sarkar and Shambhu Nath Dutta.																								Sarkar, an 85-year-old freedom fighter, was allegedly given urine when she pleaded for drinking water in custody. 																								A division bench issued todays directive after the petitioners counsel contended that the rights panel did not take on record statements of various witnesses, including the trio.
